Dov Carmel (Hebrew: דוב כרמל) is a composer and arranger (born Budapest, 1932), who began producing compositions during the 1960s.
His studies were interrupted by the Holocaust between 1944 and 1945, but he was able to resume them afterwards.
Between 1954 and 1971 he taught at schools in Israel, including 1971-1992 at Oranim.
He won the ACUM Prize in 1969 for orchestral composition and the  Kibbutz Movement Competition Prize in 1972.
